user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Cal Cohen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYyjzI0behNDtmO7PzpUsM-zMvPOQLH6JBZhMTAU_xWnDexg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best brunch in all of Israel! Went for breakfast and got the Pancakes, the egg and cheese, and the lavender latte. They do an amazing job at making the latte so flavorful without making it too sweet. The pancakes were amazing and had a very good berry topping. The egg and cheese was also so flavorful and had these sweet caramelized onions on top that was the perfect addition. Amazing music and very friendly waiters/waitresses. Perfect atmosphere! 11/10 experience highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shira Salton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKra5Gk0SJjsuJbGNKZXE9tWUNarQnwfQjrWZDa7dGADIx29A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favourite places in Tel Aviv(but only on weekdays!!). The food and coffee are excellent, and everything is of the highest quality. However, the prices are quite high ,especially those of the drinks(27 shekels for matcha!!). Great vegan options, sweet and savoury. On weekends it tends to be very crowded and the wait might last a long time, which isn't so fun on sunny or rainy days. So I recommend visiting on weekdays when the traffic is much lighter.  The service varies between excellent and poor, depends on the waiter. Recommended!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAIYfm-NWNZu5uDB2CbqfSdUL5brNlMEEf6mBl&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"Olga Kostur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzkWunUFnZuZCe6KJr-bugW8_58qizbx2Q_eiv4obn3CIuUB80Fw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing breakfast place! Vibrant, lots of people, and music is playing! The staff is attentive ❤️

Food was great as well, fantastic design of the menu  - healthy and classical options with an original take on them. Pancakes, granola, bagels!

Oat and almond-rice milk available, which is fantastic for us :))","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGNfVCk7MfCgTksCU0tJJxFUkZ2P2T6L3elPML&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2022-10-21"},{"Name":"jacob goldshtein","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXo72d68fWM6K2GxspfvmUh2C6GW9u0MathakLJYn4klK3TGrhnxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely amazing brunch experience in Tel Aviv. Food was amazing, drinks were delicious, staff was super friendly and place was beautiful. Can’t recommend this place enough especially if your a bagel lover. Would definitely return again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPw72mMhlaXs7roDU8GC2Ni8QID3PXhPwSnjkvk&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2023-5-7"},{"Name":"לילך-גולדי מרגולין","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOXObyZLDhmvq9pA4EFHgX0Jg5KH3LCHheMfILYY-AT6J1bJk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We waited for more than 30 minutes just for 2 bagels. The “Eggs N’ Cheese Bagel” was supposed to include a fried runny egg, and the egg was fully cooked.
We asked all 5 waiters for water and, at last, one of them brought it.
In addition for service not being amazing, we were emotionally pressured to add a service fee (tip, which is not included) and also the minimum fee is at 10%. The waitress literally said “our salary is only tips”..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdFNCvk2lodOzU6GA2-OKz-HzEulUSwqwUVChC&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"Franco Ruben Vargas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYrVmui_HIvy7EN7K2x-zOiGfZKqTrPNFh5nDhxBq7OmJxcUI3aA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious place for a gluten free, vegetarian or dairy free options. The place is quiet and nice with a self service concept. You order in the front counter and you pick up in the bar. All of their options are delicious and healthy from main courses to beverages. Pick from different milk alternatives and be clear if you want the GF or totally vegan options. Recommended for breakfast at anytime. I had pancakes and bagels at 3 pm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORrvXpbFMAqnPLD9hpajQ3o454gnB_STCC6dZH&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2022-3-23"},{"Name":"Epolina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKij04P_BqvHAkkyfVJqz8x79730MHkBNjo7E4iggbvBo8xLgCDA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I went twice in the past week. First time I ordered pancakes that were delicious.
Second time I ordered the famous beer bread breakfast dish. Unfortunately, it was not good. Toasted bread with sauce and fried egg was nice, but nectarine was absolutely unripened, sour, very thick and hot from the egg. I barely could eat it. Now looking back, I should've returned it.
I thought to take over star out because of it. But the place is so nice and cozy, friendly staff, quick service and superb coffee.
My advice: please use ripe fruits and thinner cuts.
Upd. I went today again, ordered pink granola, it was very pretty, but for my taste the dish was very unbalanced, a little bit chia pudding, that is tasteless and a lot of granola, couldn't finish half of it, fruits also were not sweet.
Sorry that I didn't order a bagel, looked much more promising. Taking one star off.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR-NrvGXHZq5oTPAao2uM5CTyyKBIillx5sMx6&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2020-7-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Bar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_LVV_ck0ipJg_C1WVU9PBNAWTKEtaYEDYpGbSP6Ghhh_4Yg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fresh, young, positive, atmospheric, busy, hyper Tel-Avivian coffee shop. Both coffee and food are top notch, made with love and attention to detail.
Note that you should stand in line to order, then you sit and wait for the counter to call your name. Great place for soaking some local atmosphere and people watching. If you see a long line (sometimes reaching the street), don’t get discouraged, as service is pretty fast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYXjL-nJ6CIVSNrNPyV6TGqUOSZcGtZvKI5A6M&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2022-6-12"}]

[{"Name":"Stefanie Amini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDXuPQXPFx9xs49o0U_WNjIPJREkzGok5bJ-jASjp6A4L1qLE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food, high quality products and lovely staff! They make you feel at home and never want to leave. The gravlax French toast is a must when there. But everything is tasty so you can’t go wrong. They even give a slice if cake with every coffee order. Nice touch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO_hgYAnVmyErLkr1roc3wjpm9ftJfOnPJjRid&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2023-6-25"},{"Name":"Jenny Hanna Adlerblum","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmYlLjY8Ngb-JCx0PNOcS1myd8IywoecyKoWmpowYCjKQMtMM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Perfect coffee! The food is great. Everything is tasty. You order one or two dishes and you belly will be full!! The chesse tost it's super good and i combine it with a salad. The people are nice and have great atmosphere where you can feel you are not in israel.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnSFbfCjJ202BNfOT1s2lnXdveBlKS7-Jjy5RE&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2022-12-20"},{"Name":"Nina Verzhbolovich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnM1k2nBo-ehhHqsl-ax03-K9FyfIKp1YjPtfhVSK-9ejvx1uI6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I won’t even bother you with a long review. I just don’t feel like sharing The World’s Best Almond Croissant with any of you. He is the king. Huge, fatty, filled with almonds on both sides, crunchy outside and soft inside, that piece of art, combined with great coffee and a smile, gave me a sense of hope. And yes, I haven’t tried the rest of the pastries yet","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTEDKPTw0EP7JuQb_8dKe0RauDBcuY2NhdyO67&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2022-10-27"},{"Name":"Lidor Bracha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhu-e9PG1FRpcj5hIbUOSgYPR6z3dTcn5gNTfFEjFxBz064ivU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New place in Tel Aviv.
The place serves excellent breakfasts and coffees. All of the pastries are super fresh and delicious.
The price is low and that’s unique.
We had a good time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdaBsZG1BYZqK8LV4TrOlb15TGwUAdK0M7gC9o&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2022-3-18"},{"Name":"Lihi Bavli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We decided to give this place a try after reading all those excellent reviews and quite frankly we were a bit disappointed.
We came at an evening hour and we’re told that many of the pastries are already not available we tried the spinach pastry with egg and a salad which was both only OK.
After that we tried two of the desserts which looked great but again were only OK (and actually gave us a flashback to the 90s).
Service was price though and we had to ask for things a few times and the toilet was kind of dirty actually.
I know we won’t be back at this place but I guess it will succeed because it’s kosher and there aren’t a lot of kosher options in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhO_R42H8ilpoIFnQqok-GVZdMdm0YTRI4QkFB&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2022-8-19"},{"Name":"Keren Novik Cohen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3-HAYH6-Ek_kCqhF5_PEaPof_WwVd6DR3eXX839iHmyXhStqkXg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super breakfast.  All ingredients are fresh. It's very tasty . Highly recommended 👌","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8Zus8zrmWiEDWtILMrE6C9ZpyyV6A1veiM34O&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2023-1-25"},{"Name":"yvan lang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU013aBzdTueGPX896tGj8elk6t0HUSnz6_HUn2zPMxEG-wiV_V=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Just a first impression.
2 coffee, 2  pastries. Everything was well done and fresh if not amazing. Maybe the fruit salad was a bit weird in the presentation.
Lots of people around us with cakes, salads and cooked eggs. They all seems to enjoy themselves.
Intend to go back for more tasting","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5YMwyZeEp4-g2VLLXK7_5y11T9kIsuTWYX5iO&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2022-12-11"},{"Name":"Itai Norman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1NdNAAy5lx9I0LVg_Ru8zCMOvR2UWcsRsiVNKzPzi5w1exg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favorites in the "Old North" of Tel Aviv.
We came here for breakfast, had coffee and two dishes.
Coffee was good but the best part is the big, tasty and decent priced food.
Avocado toast was great and so were the pancakes.
I also recommend the French toast with the mascarpone & berries , wow!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPo5WFDE72Dnk3tiGXTLhwnR9-CeILvwflw0fAG&fid=0x0:0xaaf40b8a26986f31"],"When":"2022-8-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Rupert A.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLc1z9bLynhgKGkihxX-cpS9pSPodymkNd2IFPssLXm5QGQeA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What stood out most to me was the friendly and attentive service by the host.  He was genuinely friendly and caring.
Please note that they have a "happy hour" on alcoholic beverages as well as a special lunch menu from noon till 4pm.
We arrived at 3:45 pm but missed it since it took them till after 4pm to take our order.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzFBJk0J-gYyvcQiA_Idt5ej6TP7w1VT-1OYL-&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2022-3-24"},{"Name":"Caitlin Treloar-Ward","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVz0pnrLHBCbxLUIdjyGRBdtKcUCRz_Y6K8G3IQGyP3qI7lQqQhbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Beautiful little spot, expansive menu for small and large dishes.
Calabrese toasted sandwich and the shakshuka were ordered.
When we went to pay, we weren’t asked to leave a tip or had the option, our card was swiped and we were off. Sorry about that, we would have liked to have done the right thing 🌈","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCqX54uCPAHyrxEwU6DzlLG7ZQ_4YE-bC4EpHE&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2022-7-30"},{"Name":"Alex Frazier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB5LMa-E6QAUeiAzedbdJCbkyB008tb5iNbqOOcbmrM8yjBVPz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dizengoff Cafe is a great place to stop in for a quick coffee, or to stay for breakfast or lunch. The inside is very cute and the patio is the perfect place to sit and people watch. I highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxhZMHzWqavWzwOZP2mJPwiC4uLuYLcz9m4Wct&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2023-9-26"},{"Name":"Niv Shimoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKC_NTN_3jBQaO39EWMTRMDNxltkCNxFPlx77COe2wTH3h1sHifA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A great coffee shop in the middle of Dizengoff St. The decoration of the place is very delicate and beautiful. I really like the atmosphere, this is one of the best things in this city. food was excellent, I ate the Roasted Salad and it was very special. the flavors are very surprising, fresh and refreshing. what I like the most is the taste of the ginger in the salad dressing.
The bruschetta was tasty but overpriced. staff is friendly and polite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlNK8wu1BE2UYmpoB9ch_grfgdSJPe86D54Tcf&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2018-2-27"},{"Name":"Mindaugas Vaiskunas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXV1XstWgpKxn2Yaz_x7eoE23j4XXMZpfRRBVyEm84evAqdXK9sVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of visiting Cafe Dizengoff, and I must say, it was an excellent experience. The cafe has a cozy atmosphere that immediately made me feel comfortable and welcome. The food was absolutely delicious, and I was particularly impressed with the shakshuka with feta and the toast with gouda and buche cheese. It's not surprising that Cafe Dizengoff is a popular destination, as the food and atmosphere are both great. I highly recommend this cafe to anyone looking for a delicious meal in a warm and inviting setting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAFrAR_dahjRB56SrLPoZ6S5svV_Z9iGGz31P9&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2023-3-20"},{"Name":"Mary Grant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXG4TwuDMP1JtCNcJ2Mj_TGPANaoLorac7uFTUhqD5rD-iZNg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A big choice of breakfast dishes as well as regular menu. We tried crispy chicken sandwich and Mesahan (chicken on the bread with tahini and species). Both dishes were huge, we didn’t manage to finish it. The sandwich was nothing special, came with a spicy sauce - I would not recommend to take it. Mesahan was very unique mix of tastes and spices, we’ve never tried anything like this. It was also very filling and good for sharing.

The place was full on Friday afternoon, all tables outside were taken. Amazing vibes and a lovely view on a busy Dizengoff street.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQ1XsLnPlOUkBXO2cTBN37DFbfvGu-p6YtMZZY&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2023-3-31"},{"Name":"Lihi Bavli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been here multiple times for breakfast afternoon coffee or dinner. I love the variety of the menu and all dishes or very good, fresh and tasteful. The service is always great and I really love the music.
It does get a little bit busy sometimes you have to wait in line for a table.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLx4uDms2n4wAb0R8ufDwQgEoytJtmyf1vVHh-&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2021-8-17"},{"Name":"michelle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU28g7bMDgS8xYgyafala8XDJKUjNo4MDVxjdxqxwuCwiyleCuSTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"food was great and the portions were even better- the single breakfast was huge! a nice inexpensive stop for breakfast with an authentic tel avivian atmosphere. The service was amazing and they even handed us free ice cream since it was so hot outside! Only thing is the place is usually really crowded and in our case the people that sat beside us really didn’t respect personal space so it wasn’t the greatest experience in that aspect- unfortunately we couldn’t really converse or eat properly because they were constantly smoking right on us and talking loudly. It’s not the cafe’s fault but do keep in mind that the place could get crowded especially on Fridays.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmuXj0vWB2tNgQZTf9W2oW5UfESZ95kr1jgPIQ&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2021-6-4"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Juanjo Soler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuMlM6lfvalDI2OsoROFdQImCED3593l0r3IHyZjYPMx8s2aw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious brunch in the Carmel market area. Typical Israeli dishes full of flavour and very generous. The place has outdoor as well as indoor seating space and the vibe is really cool and welcoming. Staff were super friendly too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3GLDquGLCY_0rRnNdB7H4vluaIjhwGYmxIWuk&fid=0x0:0x79369abaab6923ff"],"When":"2023-4-4"},{"Name":"Alex Issokson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoRJyA_Xs9u3cxcLQYprhe6GUotpDDn7TxBuIAqZrrePjD5kxR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Some of the best food I've eaten in Israel! I ordered the brisket sandwich and it was truly excellent. The brisket was of a high quality, bursting with flavor and heat (not spicy, but temperature-wise). The pickles added a great touch as well. The other members of my party had the smoked salmon and avocado sandwich which they said was excellent. Two people tried the chocolate chip cookie (cookie) which was okay. It was better once they asked it to be warmed up.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpaJVAUgsonEsF493doGnb3AkJtIzZEjMKPu81&fid=0x0:0x79369abaab6923ff"],"When":"2022-12-30"},{"Name":"Lihi Bavli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute little café near Carmel market. A little crowded on the outside on Fridays and plus there’s space to seat inside of one wants to (it is more popular however to wear outside obviously).
The food is good, and so is the coffee, but the service is a bit slow and the restrooms were in a terrible state. Maybe it’s better when it’s less crowded.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgF-jdqdZcZcVCoceNCAuexuBNP9trmdViL3SM&fid=0x0:0x79369abaab6923ff"],"When":"2022-10-7"},{"Name":"Diana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYoGBqpoHzrK-LrRKzer5LeDNPCczzAlg_xxwlbVFlLOOZNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really liked the vibe of this place. It’s always really full but we still enjoyed our meal. The açai bowl was served with granola and date syrup which tasted sooo good! The saluf and eggplant tasted also really good","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPk02sfL3xG6owlCdbHpZk3LGJHfOXwHPwpju3&fid=0x0:0x79369abaab6923ff"],"When":"2023-9-21"},{"Name":"Joe D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgkdaMaa6oQUGvwVbU2u1_WpC1GKx38b0PMlhcwc7Rz_Y4Dg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The brunch was very tasty. It was quite busy so we had to wait a long time for the menu, ordering, food, etc. Nevertheless, people are friendly and it is a nice place to sit outside and enjoy the lively streets of Tel Aviv.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9w8oVPjBPwAKY3gAxM8s1v3pBHYRUp3mQUHPV&fid=0x0:0x79369abaab6923ff"],"When":"2023-5-22"},{"Name":"Noam Firuz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM6T6K3RQONRCfyxAZw6JE0UyWLQxqNhTpjfOVkaOs0ilWw0Qt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome place!
.
1) The staff are very friendly and kind.
2) The food was delicious, I ate the Avocado & Salmon sandwich, it was absolutely amazing.
They use very good bread.
3) The location is great, and the music are definitely set up some good vibes.

Plus, I came to work with my laptop, and they are very friendly regarding people who comes to work and enjoy nice atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZ1CD4Nv6D69qQdlZZaioWmvDGTuCMNwHiami-&fid=0x0:0x79369abaab6923ff"],"When":"2017-12-8"},{"Name":"Ananas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvSY_0CcUHWW58CoAUab3IYnP5xLLWeIrwgd1uwzIiikBw9XI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place for brunch with amazing local specialties. There's something in the menu for every taste, both on the sweet and on the savoury side. I really enjoyed the eggplant dish and the yogurt. Service was extremely nice despite the restaurant being fairly busy. [{"Name":"Shira Salton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKra5Gk0SJjsuJbGNKZXE9tWUNarQnwfQjrWZDa7dGADIx29A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The coffee is very good, and the place is really nice. However, the chocolate chip cookie I tried was quite dry and not so tasty. The price is average to a specialty coffee in Tel Aviv. I had bought some beans which were great, but when I had asked whether it's fare trade the cashier had no idea what I was talking about. So I'm pretty sure it's not fare trade;) Nice place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUKkQqliGvK7iVYlVucLBe5sX5F9YHCyhQa44I&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2023-9-26"},{"Name":"RAVE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZkEtNCn047-jM4dPo37rcR69TYzKQQ9RPQ0ETwVOXUhBSVz89Sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Updating 😁 it’s been a while, I hope that now everybody is welcome as I do like this place.

Unfortunately I had to change my review, i’ve been thrown away after sitting in this coffee shop many times saying that “ you can’t get in if you eating non-kosher food” 😱
I find it very disturbing when people allow themselves to be racist or homophobic or whatever extreme idea it was.
The same way that I would never tell somebody that he cannot get into the place because he only eats kosher food it is not OK to say the opposite if my views are different.
I decided to put three stars instead of one to allow them to apologize and civilized.

One of my favorite coffee shops in Tel Aviv, i’d like it because it’s both casual and very chic.
I love spending time there at my morning and have my luxury coffee :) it’s super tasty and super high-quality.
The coffee is deep in flavor and made to perfection.
They should definitely upgrade their sandwiches but nothing will stop me from grabbing another cup of coffee at this place.
I just love it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlHhFwTYSr_NPDZHhvfj-n2G8wl6YL3RHBNmX4&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2018-7-1"},{"Name":"Ido Simyoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzkOoy_rh-Crbnc6Ql2Y0qqZ1-C34qzmepjSCd8YvsG7BJRyG8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stunning professional with  hipster vibe coffeeshop. Loved my oat milk latte . Bought even coffee to take home to nyc with me. I like that they asked me if I wanted it in a mug or glass (glass rules). Service was beyond friendly","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_lI9Ae4olBolAEi9vDbqkhOwCY2JM43DenhLg&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2022-5-6"},{"Name":"Michael Olshansky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXX61wd2boH8NVva-SQMZH9kDolVUM2Mh4GZQmKDkjjh_pkPgNVew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Seriously the best coffee in the area. Not your typical Aroma experience (bo-oring). Hi tech kids and hip Tel Avivians surround you. I definitely recommend for a refreshing break or just an informal meeting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYnAt1246ERntTia064Se4yZ2BaSfKr_AgY4M8&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2019-1-26"},{"Name":"Bene Garcia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIY9M6ia4pGO8GpCGP2uE1q8bmJg6Ksba8vXYh1YeVGKIHUcbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best damn coffee in Israel, in days! Definitly up there with any hipster shop anywhere in the world. Got the grey blend, supposed to be tilting bitter. But it's awesome- crema is good, oil is good, temp is good, atmosphere is good. I'd give it 7-stars if i can. Worth a visit, worth a repeat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuU02vG6fhEeI8i-9o_NIbdfNG8DhC5ZxVGGVN&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2022-11-22"},{"Name":"Adam Shoshani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHVDy4icfezelaHD7P9ssa0n8bEG3hlx5dNkFj4enZVXsClatlRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"WayCup Mikveh is probably my favorite coffee shop in Tel-Aviv. Where do I start?

The coffee is roasted locally and is simply delicious. WayCup offers a range of changing single-origin coffee beans from around the world prepared in a range of brewing methods.

The owners and the baristas are some of the nicest and most friendly people around, in short, people who love what they do (coffee) and about their customers.

Whether you are just stopping by for a quick coffee (it's literally 3 min walk from Rothschild Blvd.) or if you want to open a laptop and work there for the day, highly recommend this place. Enjoy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOA11ReK7nOJTns2rkMkCEIXiZnfSjaXQWQ_siD&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2018-11-6"},{"Name":"Roy Paz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJXf90d-wMIdjDpYOFXlZvkuY2O5UIv4YLe9fmaFpCOwemroeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally got around to giving WayCup Coffee a shot after hearing great things about it for over a year now.....
And I'm happy to report that they definitely live up to the hype! 🙃

I came here this morning to get one iced coffee and a small pastry. The plan was to order, pay, & enjoy the coffee and cigarettes while sitting at the tables outside, & then heading off to begin the rest of my day...

I ended up staying here for about 3 1/2 hours without even fully noticing (or caring)😋.
The coffee here is absolutely perfect & the prices are standard /average for a Tel Avivian coffee shop. But the thing that makes WayCup unique in my opinion is; a) the people here - (the workers as well as the customers), & b) how friendly they are...

The other customers I met while sitting at the table outside were so friendly and laid back, that my introverted, shy, & quiet self, ended up speaking to 3 different, random people who I've never met before & it felt completely natural.

Each of the 3 people chose to sit right next to me - at the table directly next to mine. - these 3 people came separately & at different times obviously) and there was such a friendly vibe + straight up good conversations with random strangers.

One was an amazing artist who was drawing while drinking his coffee, the 2nd person is an employee at Facebook who was really interesting and cool to speak with, & the 3rd person was just a cool woman (I didn't ask what she does haha).

Anyways I ended up ordering two more coffees because they were so delicious and I was thoroughly enjoying myself....

So from my original plan of a quick iced coffee + one little pastry before heading off, I had 3 coffees with the pastry and stayed for 3+hrs.

*THE MAIN REASON I VISITED WAYCUP COFFEE IN THE FIRST PLACE*:

They're one of the VERY few places in Israel that sell Flat Whites (...if not the only one? - I honestly can't say for sure because l really haven't looked into it; but it's definitely the only coffee shop I've ever seen in Israel with Flat White on the menu).

The coffee is strong, fresh, & extremely tasty.
It's honestly addicting in a way that other coffees aren't.

All in all:
A) Great service
B) Great pastries
C) Great atmosphere
D) What else could you ask for?

By far one of the best Coffee Shops in this city. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Sivan Omer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQFcQrT9HYnj6kQ-6Df-7VBGK7K9oXN2R7i96z1Wiw6fhGwg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We waited almost 1 hour as it is Friday and they are not taking reservations but at least we enjoyed! The stuff is very kind and they offer us iced tea while we wait.
We couldn’t decide on breakfast or lunch so we ordered both eggs and chicken, everything was delicious and we would definitely come back to try more dishes :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM52w7ALuYsu9GybUekGQye0rCKp75VScfFuoUx&fid=0x0:0xc957a8934e00a8c6"],"When":"2023-7-7"},{"Name":"Gabe Kagan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLh_4e_xTjKryN4ANOTtvPOE2yqNJ355skVWFZ_IjJLOrM9wg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cafe 38 in Tel Aviv is an absolute gem that sparkles in every aspect! From the moment you step in, the vibrant ambiance sets the perfect tone for a delightful dining experience. The coffee here is an art form, with each sip delivering a burst of flavor and a comforting aroma that lingers. Their menu is a culinary masterpiece, offering an array of delectable dishes that cater to all palates. Whether you're a health-conscious foodie or an indulgent connoisseur, Cafe 38 has something to tantalize your taste buds.

The service is unparalleled - warm, attentive, and genuinely caring. The staff goes above and beyond to ensure every guest feels welcomed and cherished. But what truly stood out was the exceptional sommelier, who skillfully guided us through the wine list, elevating our dining experience to new heights.

Beyond the delicious offerings, Cafe 38 also boasts a charming ambiance, adorned with tasteful decor and cozy seating arrangements that make you feel right at home. Whether you're catching up with friends, working remotely, or simply savoring a moment of solitude, this cafe provides the perfect backdrop.

The attention to detail here is remarkable, from the presentation of each dish to the thoughtful touches that make the experience truly unforgettable. Cafe 38's commitment to quality shines through in every aspect, making it a sparkling beacon among Tel Aviv's culinary scene.

In summary, Cafe 38 is an exquisite haven for coffee enthusiasts, foodies, and wine aficionados alike. With its delightful blend of flavors, impeccable service, and charming ambiance, this cafe is a must-visit destination for anyone seeking a remarkable dining experience in Tel Aviv. I can't recommend it enough!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTUdwXR2mQg6JqklTTeb33WnlA-qsYo3dx9Z8E&fid=0x0:0xc957a8934e00a8c6"],"When":"2023-8-2"},{"Name":"Lior Shamir","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlnzjk1iMi_Ry6NIzmtBbegEA33NMrlnovUNaTtEAA5S_l4zk3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful beautiful place. The inside is gorgeous, the outside is looking onto a calm street, very calming area and great coffee and sweets. Hope to try the food next time! Thank you 🫶🏼","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Margo Belyaeva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9seRNgDZoTeT0-R0C_8-eDLOrD-alQ2Vm5Um500oeIRq9hX9Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Perfect place for brunch/breakfast.
I love la shuk and cucu and I was so happy to see that there’s a new place from the same chain.
Food was good, I took croque madam and my husband took hashbrowns. Both were a little bit overgrilled but the taste was good and it wasn’t like a usual Israeli breakfast that I liked about the place.
The service was AMAZING! We got a table in 5 min + chair for a kid and food came quickly. Also the gave us napkins!! Which is so unusual for Tel Aviv cafes.
I definitely recommend it.
Next time I’d take also French toast - it like soooo good","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcCeCKBCIb_F0B1adwHPc4UU5vYFl_CvL-6US5&fid=0x0:0xc957a8934e00a8c6"],"When":"2023-6-28"},{"Name":"Eric Berberich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWF8hKJUr7Xjti44PYZFQgNqCiE1gn-eMoN2WO5C7a-Y50OuEgnxA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In the location of the "Shine".. Which was an institution.. And this iteration follows this tradition... The renewed atmosphere and the dishes will soon be renowned in the city. Surely coming again soon","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWn2_m_tPwqXsf_CKs2wN6XmcdNmTOs2fy7nBZ&fid=0x0:0xc957a8934e00a8c6"],"When":"2023-9-22"},{"Name":"Lidor Bracha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhu-e9PG1FRpcj5hIbUOSgYPR6z3dTcn5gNTfFEjFxBz064ivU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! What an amazing delicious place.
We had a great time. Don’t you ever skip the mini pancakes with caviar.
Staff were nice and price was fair.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mayan R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJoSuVu0o9pM7gG-c8eRti79Y-ftnRbwys0ojkOH30qEGINWAcnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a cute, quaint spot for quality food and a chill vibe!
We stopped by for happy hour which was I believe from 5 till 7 (?) on a weekday, offering 25% off the entire menu. Not a bad deal at all!
The food was fantastic! We got the ricotta and spinach tortellini— by far my favorite and absolutely worth ordering! In addition, we ordered the broccoli dish which was also really tasty!
As for drinks, we had the espresso martini—
Turned out to be a bit more milky than desirable— and some gin concoction that the waiter recommended for its refreshing taste. Both cocktails were mediocre, we felt pretty neutral about those.
Location-wise it’s perfect! Very centrally-located near Kikar Dizengoff but not too central that it’s in the middle of city chaos.
Highly recommend this cafe for delicious food and a pleasant vibe.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elad G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4rBup20rfPqs42fVZ6R0tftg2HTHKm1pWxln7GqryRK1Tkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely new local coffee and breakfast place.
The menu is well built, and the dishes are made with extra attention to the details.
The staff are super nice, and the atmosphere is great

Will definitely give it another visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOzk_6XolTTL32gxI1-__3TEUGZh3sgaPwYp1M&fid=0x0:0xc957a8934e00a8c6"],"When":"2023-7-15"}]

So special, hipsterish with seducing cool 😎 vibes. The coffee was delicious as well as their pastries. Staff was incredible, very friendly and accommodating. I have lost my sunglasses 😎 there and they returned them to me. I will never forget this genuine gesture. I wish to be back soon! Highly recommend! I LOVE YOU GUYS 💜","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrY_afSMGpE3tO8pF8amHlQfylPenkipUnR4Bn&fid=0x0:0xbb3f8fd4b85ecc87"],"When":"2023-5-3"},{"Name":"Jessica Gosse (Jess)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqfjFEPH-e1RyTFxLPiwr4WsGid04XVgxW4GoJXd7Pas9CP10F=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Laid back, simple yet captivating, I had a great experience getting coffee and a pastry from there. It's the place you feel welcomed and you know nobody will rush you to leave. The only sad thing was that the cinnamon babka was lacking cinnamon, but it was delicious nonetheless!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marco Tullio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX61tPZxnJLUG9b6kaeht8E4Rpkvo7bJ0VV4wBCQBvP1bcxD_De1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Let me tell you about this amazing cafe in the Florentin neighborhood of Tel Aviv. Not only does it serve delicious tuna sandwiches and cappuccinos, but it also boasts a lush and green ambiance with plenty of plants. It's the perfect place to relax and enjoy your favorite book under the shade of beautiful trees.

This cafe has created a tranquil oasis amidst the bustling streets of Florentin. The abundance of plants creates a refreshing and calming atmosphere that invites you to unwind and escape into your own little world. With cozy seating areas nestled under the trees, you can find the perfect spot to settle in with your book and enjoy some quiet time.

When it comes to the food and drinks, this cafe doesn't disappoint. Their tuna sandwiches are packed with flavor and made with fresh ingredients. Whether you prefer a classic recipe or a unique twist, each bite will leave you satisfied. And of course, don't forget to pair your sandwich with a delicious cappuccino for the ultimate treat.

Not only is this cafe a haven for bookworms and plant lovers, but it also captures the essence of the Florentin neighborhood. Its laid-back and friendly atmosphere reflects the artistic and bohemian vibe of the area, making it a favorite spot among locals and visitors alike.

So, if you're looking for a unique and enchanting cafe in Florentin, Tel Aviv, where you can enjoy mouthwatering tuna sandwiches and cappuccinos amidst a green oasis, this is the place for you. Grab your favorite book, find a cozy spot under the trees, and immerse yourself in the serene ambiance of this delightful cafe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdYom6ZJA1_nFdSdO54r8QIUWwLiVrlTNCpocu&fid=0x0:0xbb3f8fd4b85ecc87"],"When":"2023-6-11"},{"Name":"Niv Shimoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKC_NTN_3jBQaO39EWMTRMDNxltkCNxFPlx77COe2wTH3h1sHifA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Florentin neighborhood well know as a hipster and cool place. beautiful coffee with fantastic seating area in and out side. the inside is old style decoration very gentle and clean. the service is good and it’s open from early morning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVFDSu-oiW05t_ptysN7ueHtcO3EbuEWrdW-BV&fid=0x0:0xbb3f8fd4b85ecc87"],"When":"2021-6-10"},{"Name":"Ermis Makis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPJYBFuTNy9p6e73zqGQhvA6fb6h_kDbsWCQ5Y8g32hSAfDgY8sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A lively, hipstery, corner café that serves great pastries and coffee. Pastries come out strong, coffee was nothing special. Gets quite full, service could be better - just impersonal. Worth a try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5O4dKKgCOHOh6Yg3tEERRnlGPw4q8MTLpZ6_7&fid=0x0:0xbb3f8fd4b85ecc87"],"When":"2023-4-9"},{"Name":"Polly Alluf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1ksNDnDtPC1yP7MRj9jtiQJa4FxffAcebYPgz3-G2y9K5Efck=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good wibe place. Sometimes hard to find a spot to sit but that's part of the charm. Great cold Americano and the selection of bakery option is one of the best in town.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steve Blake","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxdgmLn0_BeKgtrZl4PGFs4oZEjMCByBD6UDDS6x2m0n389A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute little cafe in the heart of Florentin. It has little sitting space outside and inside and it’s quite friendly. Coffee was good, and their sandwiches, although a bit small, were tasty too. Friendly service and great place overall","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBLxmJ93SoLYkHbZux4BHHbiV6ew8GB_BD5edC&fid=0x0:0xbb3f8fd4b85ecc87"],"When":"2018-12-12"}]

The place is perfect for working, having a family lunch  or grabbing a quick coffee! They offer a variety of options including gluten-free food! ✅
Coffee is one of the best I’ve tried in Tel Aviv, and so is the food, tasty and fresh😋. The portions are large portions and the staff is always friendly, even when the restaurant is packed.
Prices are very affordable and they have plugs everywhere!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMBQC5JhKlH89WJa3w52FnQ710okPoes94OaVq&fid=0x0:0xf6a666e1935349cf"],"When":"2021-6-18"},{"Name":"Mindaugas Vaiskunas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXV1XstWgpKxn2Yaz_x7eoE23j4XXMZpfRRBVyEm84evAqdXK9sVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Cafe Shneor and had an amazing breakfast experience. The Shakshuka and Bagel with salmon were both absolutely delicious and exceeded my expectations. I was also impressed by the speed of service - my food arrived quickly and was piping hot. The staff were incredibly friendly and accommodating, making us feel welcome. Overall, I was thoroughly impressed and would highly recommend it to anyone looking for a delicious breakfast with great service in a welcoming environment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6taKEbOVfeKmIfQv4tf57IGgTMMG8MqU2bvQU&fid=0x0:0xf6a666e1935349cf"],"When":"2023-3-17"},{"Name":"Oren Salzman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsszqe0gtbMWXVs8yX1MDHs-CjIdhhgmG4t4EPjvgmwyUMHU5C0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An hidden gem in the heart of Tel Aviv, nice service and good food. Wait time could be a bit longer because it is a small place but all in all it was a really nice place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_B_RY9PZd8DIaN9SmqL2OKHBzCILDd8thXvnv&fid=0x0:0xf6a666e1935349cf"],"When":"2023-7-8"},{"Name":"Gaby Wimsett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLS7K77pTZRdTsMKqHJfGPLiT7T9LYquMLOmH3dFgakIqQsxA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great spot for breakfast or lunch. It was one of the best coffees we had in Tel Aviv. The lunch and mimosas were great and the shakshuka is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjn7-gCChgky-NJb3_e3wlTrc980dLWlN4NDP8&fid=0x0:0xf6a666e1935349cf"],"When":"2023-9-7"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Itay C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJpuSfQh4txU0XjNyABG_cZ8dAGB7iCbxqpccBeeoUhmhUrOw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A hidden gem in the heart of Tel Aviv. Located inside The Norman hotel is a quality cocktail bar that serves dishes directly from the hotel's restaurant. No reservations needed and the place is always fairly empty, essentially one of Tel Aviv's best kept secrets.

The lokus fillet dish (grouper fish) was delicious, cocktails refreshing and well prepared. Bread pudding dessert was divine. Immaculate service, if a bit slow. Pricey, as one expects from a hotel restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkJXZnHD_laegtfyEjxBMLhU78xmMPI9or39ct&fid=0x0:0x484fba9ba0573a21"],"When":"2019-9-18"},{"Name":"Yotam Kadishay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVV3xsk5TmnUQ5kTHcBO9wVPuhyehttCaxLCuFvJ8AVngPlvbxpJw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cocktails quality wise and service - it’s a five.
But the overall vibe is more of a hotel-lobby-restaurant-waiting-library-waiting kinda place.
Meaning I wouldn’t go spend a full night there, but as a gateway drug to dinnings or alena it is perfect.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPS0jCRned15QnrB4EyvpooV2eMKkRXjg1SlfHc&fid=0x0:0x484fba9ba0573a21"],"When":"2019-11-22"},{"Name":"Rebecca Brindza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVecen_w3nMyiOEBOg9Q3zy8LFCL76e4MOqyQGAk6ovzcdc8Htg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great spot in Tel Aviv for classic cocktails, fun fare, a 1920s vibe and spot on service. The bartenders make the best Vespers and dirty martinis in the city. You MUST try the octopus skewers cooked in lamb fat 🤤.

The bar does not take reservations, you can however make a reservation at the restaurant, Alena. We love to stopping by for lunch or evening drinks!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6qgg6C5HDus5AcpBPw-GyJpxNTW_JNpsaQv4W&fid=0x0:0x484fba9ba0573a21"],"When":"2021-7-9"},{"Name":"David Mor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUxuo5NFedyavYtAuhSS2_qQKMx6S9FpuaqgUaD2jAJ5_j8v_y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Library Bar is a lovely aristocratic style bar with a great selection of cognac drinks and a really warm atmosphere. The food that comes from the hotel restaurant, Alena, is amazing but what really blew our mind was the staff. They were super nice and chatty and they even surprised us with an extra desert! An expensive place but worth it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0ABQtcgwwDAj2_Wq3mFYNTEhWJiX6e34BQfnK&fid=0x0:0x484fba9ba0573a21"],"When":"2019-2-16"},{"Name":"Yam Mesicka","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDsHdzsTm1J3fqGcPRqEoWpSTpLOOoWiu9xn8hoeJrDlwTqtAn9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Excellent atmosphere, great cocktails.
Beautiful and fancy place with average cocktail prices, where the service can be either great or disappointing.
Absolutely best Martini in Tel Aviv. Try to stick to the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNG7QOFgfR2FssuTXF_eO4KYOqli2eXeG6HEWeq&fid=0x0:0x484fba9ba0573a21"],"When":"2019-6-17"},{"Name":"Danielle Abis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLgsfSAO8IbS_bBLDk5-v8qaNyUhbM2AF4GZm3TTAehxq4h63h=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really liked the drinks and the staff was friendly. It's also a very intimate bar with sofa seating. It's a little pricey, but not too bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-SabEYWOXmmmwQ56XT7_F0q7e4F-qsmhy1mQ&fid=0x0:0x484fba9ba0573a21"],"When":"2021-8-17"},{"Name":"Jonathan Ben Chanoch","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJEPF18weUaQHQJw2Brhdz1QpyHEfq_lYnDQJW5HIhIpM6oaA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As many people here have already said, this is a hidden gem. One of the most aesthetically pleasing bars in Tel Aviv, you'll feel like you're in a different world when you walk in.

Fantastic cocktails, great food and that special atmosphere perfect for intimate meetings or a nice date. I'd say they serve the best Vesper Martini in the city.

They do not take reservations beforehand, so I suggest showing early-ish (19:00/20:00) to make sure you have seating. If you do decide to come later you may have to wait a bit for a spot, especially during the weekends.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lev Kantor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXefIRBC7cddrRJnxaxg7Rt8FHBMyrk_awtJ4hrJu3xZ7jWNb7XCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing bar, great cocktails. Yonatan is the best barmen ever","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQyuz90-egDdiDedH_igabz-jrKUCO55t8VQai&fid=0x0:0x484fba9ba0573a21"],"When":"2021-11-28"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Nariman Loulou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLben8_T5xKSynxKHgr6Gx1ODXWjkTcOLlfxH6zEpu75KJsjM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very nice coffee shop. The vibe is nice. Very kind staff. Prices are ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMM6uX2l0EwzRVvdZU0fcWXh6kD-6wyO2q2ynV&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2022-3-12"},{"Name":"sharif sweilem","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWGdrejLm6Ql5YW4QX3BvDOnOBGGUjrZy-akNo1y3B2Jmizl5f2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's very delicious, the atmoshper is  traditional with songs of fairouz, we ordered zaatar, labnah, hummus, green zaatar with cheese and two lemonades it costs us 205 NIS","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOovmd4OyPWOvFz5LiBsIY16-a7K4K0tyRBO-Ia&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2023-7-25"},{"Name":"Yelle G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1FMysoxRDm9sVp7F5Q9GCQWIkqYq1-gCz7GP1dW8xEGxikTeU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coffee and Knafa are the most delicious ❤️ just for them you can come 😁☀️

Arabic coffee here is not just coffee. It is a deep and intense symphony of flavors, rich in spice notes, with bitterness and a slightly sweet aftertaste. It is served in traditional small cups, and each sip is imbued with oriental magic, leading to a world of soft pillows, incense and warm hospitality.

And now about Knaf. This is a sweet that can easily become the queen of any dessert table. Made with carefully selected ingredients, it is soft and tender, with a crispy golden crust and delicate sweet cheese inside. It is served warm, soaked in fragrant syrup, with the addition of fresh nuts. Now this is one of my favorite places, I recommend it to everyone ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQH_N7xePYi2TwQvpl7s45oMv1YmVq5amTuQkY&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2023-2-6"},{"Name":"Niv Shimoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKC_NTN_3jBQaO39EWMTRMDNxltkCNxFPlx77COe2wTH3h1sHifA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Authentic Arab cafe, you can feel here the warm hospitality. they are welcome and very nice. the food is ok there hummus, salads and knaffe and more from the Arab kitchen. the place located in beautiful area, the heart of old Jaffa. very special atmosphere all over the neighborhood. the sea is just 3 min walk away. they have so many Hookah taste here and almost everyone smoke.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPftf8DKExaLBXCTSdp4YLM3KBKAyJd03lV54_N&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2018-5-9"},{"Name":"Elena Serena Piccardi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKfchDorSxNYCgZhioGbYJjDrJJjUKR8CSxSbtE0PZRiaH2CVL5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We bumped into this little gem while strolling around Jaffa and had an amazing lunch! Great vegetarian options and huge portions! Smoothies also recommended! Definitely a perfect spot for a quick, recharging lunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlKtLHI8f0OZEqHw88I5cqQ0LINwQe7sycfimc&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2019-2-9"},{"Name":"joseph saadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9Hk7kNLq6-ySBhZYcoLt9vOjLsWOFWTQfS1dG8QBATcp6tpGohg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"OMG... food is really good.. good shisha.. prices are affordable.. the location is very close to the old city (two minutes on foot) and the old sea port of jaffa.. looks more local and reflects more the traditional jaffa unlike other restaurant that are made for tourists.. historically this cafe is the very same cafe that the fishing men use to sit in the thirty's of the last century when they come back from the sea in the morning..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP11dpf-UzKNG2l90xn-30lMeP07dCQnZk1ql6_&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2020-2-28"},{"Name":"Ema BUDAEVA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFUSCm5f-asXVAcW3k0MvSCR3cwQ1qJHwMaSvAB4mjEREGZHEE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Open on Saturday.
We ordered kebab. It was so hard, like stone. But the staff is nice and they agree to change plate .
So, the price is quite high for kebab - 55","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP451jIOh3bGpNS-8j-VVD9ZuwI14ytE9YPvCn&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2022-4-2"},{"Name":"Yoël Knopf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKYq7LPaFpWBqjJvW1ztipsHcxn022myz4dUZoZ48ohecbX9my=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A nice little place with a decent selection of tasty local, and some continental, dishes.  A good place to stop and relax during your day of walking/site-seeing, maybe even with a hooka/shisha/nargila.  Service can be slow at times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzL2FjFopelLtHXwU0vPk-Em2l6mgHpMRGyuoC&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2019-11-21"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Sandhya Prashant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOxN5KxhheD0dIuJwPa2eSMqi0LBfsmSQaogeVHk8C1A9TfNvXtg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly and quick service, very accommodating of special needs with their menu. Very tasty veg salad and the apple crumble. The quantity is big so order accordingly. First time seeing olives in nachos 😇","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNqXxuLmfdtnC2s7dqkqM144NoHHrQzvrcJhK-\u0026fid=0x0:0x12b8f9527befdc16"],"When":"2023-2-14"},{"Name":"Ivan Šaravanja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjYNI2VdEw0iq78X0udE6gkZu_ttpm1X2CPjEPVuwpiAz6trn2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you’re visiting Tel Aviv, I would suggest trying the local cuisine. However, if you’re craving American food, this isn’t a bad place to visit. The service is excellent, and both the location and interior are great. The only downside is the food could be better; they might consider offering a side dish with the steak instead of serving it on its own.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"SD R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXA1AVThVlTL-R_LYFaT84Xdu3bwnWmW1-l4pTT5-KvzXEhicuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you like American football - this is the place to go in Tel Aviv.  I was able to catch the Sunday afternoon (east coast) games.  It’s a fun vibe, good food and service is great.  Recommend it for the vibe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxaqJTNSsUYCHvx8pmrJrQCyothv8dI-im4wQu\u0026fid=0x0:0x12b8f9527befdc16"],"When":"2022-11-28"},{"Name":"Mark Harding","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJ5KRevFsGOc1Mgi_Oio-IrsCKcRB369IAMPzEVg4USarNrlti=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been going through a rather trying time over the past week and decided to take a day off to recharge and relax. We left home around midmorning, headed through to Tel Aviv and spent the rest of the morning strolling along the beachfront chilling. Around Lunch time we headed over to Mike's Place on the beachfront and had some of the most delicious burgers with bacon and cheese on the fries. What an awesome lunch. On leaving we ordered a Oreo Cheesecake and flattened it as soon as we got back home. We would most certainly recommend you go pay Mike's Place in Tel Aviv a visit for some delicious food with an awesome vibe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPblkP0WyN0RL5cWZtPzCb2qPS0u0cDKSSViws9\u0026fid=0x0:0x12b8f9527befdc16"],"When":"2022-1-22"},{"Name":"System 100","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKXBubI4s9ATmCGQp9I43IaXPBd_U3V5oZJ_JWaCgn9-8vM4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We ordered chicken wings for a hefty price of no less than 65ils (nearly 20usd!!) the \"wings\" arrived in a few minutes and half cold which made me wonder as I know cooking these should really take longer. They were all tiny and over cooked and not tasty. Later that evening I got bad stomach.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matas Vaitkevicius","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWz8wS5wkygC1oQTKjmXDft11mg1G7h6Q9vwx2Ox0fvVTipfdP7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great time here. Live music and insane vibes. Fantastic cocktails and wine, even when we had to wait for the waitress to show up for 20+ minutes, I will still give 5 stars. A place you come back to time after time for the very good reasons - great food, fair price for alcohol, great clients and service. The place actually makes you happy in a way you will take another drink you didn't plan too. And that's cool for me .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jacob Cherian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ1Td4E552LrbatzGubHpY22GtrguiJa7z72mWiPTvUbdPSP87v=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A Tel Aviv institution. Laid back bar with an excellent menu that changes constantly. This is not the place for refined dining, but the food is very good and on par with a casual restaurant. You can definitely go there for a meal.  And they are open every day of the week.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMncsRV9tWRhV10JT27eEd3CR1OUflwHwKkPvKD\u0026fid=0x0:0xcbe18246ea4e47d0"],"When":"2022-6-18"},{"Name":"Mushi Merdler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2jhEZGp4Vep7ahIwxuRYLKv5feDLgN4nh2ALkQZHlxFL8vlU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Real Tel Aviv atmosphere. Few dishes the eat by the beer but with a lot of thinking and great quality. Don’t look for a fancy plating. It’s a truly Tel Avivian Bar","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Olshansky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXX61wd2boH8NVva-SQMZH9kDolVUM2Mh4GZQmKDkjjh_pkPgNVew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tel Aviv is very high paced with lots of places open and close all the time. Stands out the iconic Minzar, which never disappoints with excellent beer selection, best food you can wish for (in a pub) and awesome signature vibe. Opens early on and always busy with market goers, tourists and later on with loyal crowds to finish the night. This place is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOluYsUCyPBw4EpVeyMAhKNpJae3NA37mv9JAyo\u0026fid=0x0:0xcbe18246ea4e47d0"],"When":"2019-8-10"},{"Name":"Uri Ar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMThW2KLH_F1rIFhKX6XDcZyK0YuJ8j7scN7fNXbvvG6Yt8HY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favorite spot in Tel Aviv. Good food, reasonably priced. Good service. I prefer the bar to the tables, personally.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_InQerKnD9TBkgFQ0zuBe36JWwd1_Hr80UJ3O\u0026fid=0x0:0xcbe18246ea4e47d0"],"When":"2022-6-21"},{"Name":"Ravit Shem-Tov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1oKCH59-WO1FPRgQteLa7bv1gi1tgCUXWk5znbjgBsR5ujgl5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A real Telavivian institution. Food is served from about 12:00.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPZri2luEeNn8nfPnSVUCK0w8VMWiK5gjqvKOs\u0026fid=0x0:0xcbe18246ea4e47d0"],"When":"2018-4-20"},{"Name":"Jonathan Gan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHYSmIZtqp4RNnfijEbV3Qg4dkmlrjgMeSpKNE3gLeOM008dde3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A good restaurant with the cool Tel-Aviv vibe and energy. [{"Name":"Rupert A.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLc1z9bLynhgKGkihxX-cpS9pSPodymkNd2IFPssLXm5QGQeA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Florentino is the "Soho" district of Tel Aviv.
This restaurant/bar represents the spirit of the neighborhood with funky, eclectic interior and a semi covered outdoor seating (with headlamps on cool days)

The server, Atalia, was amazing.  She is very friendly and efficient and really makes one feels welcomed.
ALL the food that we had was from their extensive VEGAN food choices of their menu.
We had a "chicken" schnitzel  cheeseburger, a burger made out of chestnuts and sweet potatoes, grilled eggplant with teaching sauce, veg salad.  The "eggs" that look taste and behave like real eggs were ALL VEGAN substitutes.
They also have a large selection of beers on tap and wines.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkieX12orddAzLacNyphDnBOeddvJUZCLZReKM&fid=0x0:0x8c862d971193a562"],"When":"2022-3-13"},{"Name":"Kiariladyboss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCEIQq7u4XLgEzL_AKtN5X92ml-ugV3sa6GTf414nIAAMrrAQF3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had dinner at Shuffle Bar and loved the food, the vibe and the service. They have many vegan options. I tries the Arais made of soy, it was delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqR5CP-qmXfsVJBH2KlmLCMF6pOWQWYX9QWzks&fid=0x0:0x8c862d971193a562"],"When":"2023-5-9"},{"Name":"Lia Ismailov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJ8VjLNFo7a5ln8VGSrTZLZM98PaPAd6KEDjYFKZtTuQj1ug=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the multiple vegan options and also the prices are very cheap but the quality is really good.
Also the board games are amazing twist to all the bars in tel aviv.
Definitely one of my favorite places!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrzngUg5OYMofR9ozvWVYxyWktTCopPqw2p689&fid=0x0:0x8c862d971193a562"],"When":"2021-9-9"},{"Name":"Michal Elia Kamal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpk1-ym1eEAPTa1gfWENIxXft7j8u_rGmhMYnzFVBYAm4tI4E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was nice, many good vegan options, the waiter that evening was super sweet and friendly, it was my first time with some friends from abroad and it was a good spot in Florentine neighborhood to take them to.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLpVYNLVwxywjxKfYNF9Rvqce-HhQMXlYTg592&fid=0x0:0x8c862d971193a562"],"When":"2023-5-2"},{"Name":"Rachel Ginsberg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlqhPtLRoUrSNCNHJWJy0tH9_nsqeLVgqE_AWgVV8HYAQPgOO-Mw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very cute and laid back bar I really liked the music there. The staff were very accommodating and happy hour is very worth it .
Happy hour - is till20:00 and you  have 50%on the alcohol and 20%on the food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnpA5tHe8KtzaEsXEd6PjiYk3ts_m1dWzfbM7B&fid=0x0:0x8c862d971193a562"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Nasma Shwahde","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkkO4SUuI3oLLpn9KaYcu9csVO0Wa2mWeRcV44K5Wlem5EIWlDFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great vibes and atmosphere, very welcoming! The food was okay but not that delicious. We ordered asado and a vegan burger.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AntonKZ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmVwg2u1JAB77EgNKCYJltd39f73rIwBsS6Kw6BkgKdfEYYiNp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I like this place a lot because it's warm inside but there are also heaters outside - very comfortable in winter. The pineapple pizza is amazing. Good selection of beers. Service is ok-ish, responsive but a bit slow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoPzMjLp525ch44UXKYOanHfhdDd1HeWbwI4D-&fid=0x0:0x8c862d971193a562"],"When":"2023-3-8"},{"Name":"Lior Weizman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvf2aikafxw_uhbObffvjPwrDRbNx2yV0akITGnGNT-FNYnCMSCw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great vegan food! [{"Name":"Rachel Ginsberg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlqhPtLRoUrSNCNHJWJy0tH9_nsqeLVgqE_AWgVV8HYAQPgOO-Mw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place in the heart of the market. They have an interesting food menu. Notice that the portions are on the smaller side. We ordered 7 dishes of food and everything was simply delicious. Shawarma, fish fillet, challah, crispy chicken, salad, and sweet potatoes fries.
The service was really good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7Xuwc5fAfAc-O51k6tVn2JspnYL-91n8PN1Ru&fid=0x0:0xdd338e66c4252668"],"When":"2022-5-2"},{"Name":"adi samorai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAD4AO9900_mWjKaVtbmclygdeAt2COSEaVNfzf6bTCQzl0FIs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best places in the FleeMarket. Excellent food and great atmosphere, friendly service. We had lots of dishes and everything was just perfect and not expensive at all.  Must take the fried zucchini and the ceviche. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMuYP3Ic-1gDWTKa2dmsG6zI2X0YCWk_UYD66b&fid=0x0:0xdd338e66c4252668"],"When":"2021-9-10"},{"Name":"Alon Shtainiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBF3Zg3ibqsrUdA9N2g6Rgi2WVmYi6s1C7Jzs89mNpTdmdZ8EoZg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The place and the atmosphere were grate. The service was all over the place and confusing. When we asked for water it took 20 minutes and after asking for water four times.
The eggplant was very good and so the sausages. The hoot potato’s were the best I have in my life. That is the resign that I gave them 4 stars.

The price was OK for TelAviv.
Please make some efforts wit the service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPO5JpKbRNn6_djEtqhy6kf2NUYgEuyubzz45PA&fid=0x0:0xdd338e66c4252668"],"When":"2020-8-28"},{"Name":"Lihi Bavli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful atmosphere during the weekend, it was lovely and vibrant, great music and crowd. [{"Name":"Itay Malleron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2hqoP3p4uxPQTsDTLQfzMQ19wDe2t1z5FWwSvzwoyQ-54G9XU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They keep 'em coming. Guinness, service and great atmosphere make this bar a hidden gem! The staff is friendly, there's a happy hour, the music is cozy, and so are the lights. It's the perfect spot to unwind with friends or enjoy a quiet drink.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqim7i7iM9z9BDzrRZxHHK8Ij4UswIIIkW038&fid=0x0:0x487d12ab97ab4e73"],"When":"2023-5-29"},{"Name":"Aviad D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPb-erSXW8l9_k9M-aH-Zva2p1xMRA3byfaThecMOMZKCQlUGb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very cool 80s 90s and present-day music Playlist. Good beats. They basically keep adding songs to a very good Playlist that's been accumulating for the past decade.

This is a very cool place. You can sit inside where it can get real crowded but always good vibes and fun, and outside it's more for right groups of couples and friends.

I like sitting at the bar. There's always what to see from there while you're enjoying a beer or a cocktail.

Best for people that are 40 and above I'd say. You can greatly enjoy it if your in your 20s and 30s too, if you don't mind sitting with the older generation.

All in all, Herzelia doesn't have many good places to go to at the moment (March 2023), and Inga is one of the rare quality places to enjoy an evening at in Herzelia.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKxlkA_Rg1MEwQpi9Vp_WuOTpzXhQpuEcPvaks&fid=0x0:0x487d12ab97ab4e73"],"When":"2023-3-31"},{"Name":"EA Locksmith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEAEiQnsOlU0gVDHVTTFVPbfeqGEjb4fy8Kae_FcMvH21uLWfx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am so glad they charge for peanuts! Imagine it was free, naa you need them handled properly with sanitation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmeLlipAY9DmHtRkwWA5q6U7h948Bg1uJztbNK&fid=0x0:0x487d12ab97ab4e73"],"When":"2018-10-3"},{"Name":"gabriella sidesaddlegeisha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFHQ9X0zyPZFrMkgMrobpmwUUUjsnl8ESvQN9QGVLNsgR_1T6r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We always have a happy time here, it's a success guaranteed place. Loved the domestic Israel beer and my friend loved the beer nuts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjKO9YAMpnQ0-NWAUbmYZ-rXXMBqs8VRTHuBlX&fid=0x0:0x8ef269bff3be5b4d"],"When":"2018-8-28"},{"Name":"Manor Zemer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZ6ez8s5L-8b5z-rJSMSAPOfKVwT2m77e5XaYfRzfPkFFa7IOTNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Perla Bar in Tel Aviv is a great place to grab a drink and relax with friends. [{"Name":"Dor Nahum","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1VBHAzFlqxgzYEF2quKqeqgmyhMMHE5z5vB3UPzW2XEmsvgdy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Fidel has an ambience to it, not seen in many places, it is a community bar, a real life, public house, where you can sit, eat drink and be merry. in my home  of California places like this are few and dear, if you're looking to stop by and have a friendly drink with some strangers I'd definitely stop by
I had two Israeli beers and paid just above 20$ well worth it for the excellent service by Yuli who was quick and responsive,
This is a well run establishment
8.5 out of 10 would visit again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMB4aQABWBEONn0VzzyLCVZzyZ-_kFlYPOvD_Sy&fid=0x0:0x923ebcbe3a13feaf"],"When":"2023-4-7"},{"Name":"Alexandr Orlov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnCSQsFqhFazyrp19ujI3NuK3sb5QEWSqYsKgo7adScHyZaTo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I liked both the drinks and the pizza both times when I visited this place. With my love for thick pizza crust, in order to feel what you eat, and not "only for one tooth", I would call their crust the ideal middle. Don't lose this guy)) ...In general, I waited a long time and followed the creation of this place, because it was opened by a man from a nearby alco-store.
And he and the girl who work with him there, consolidated the impression of not only knowledgeable people, but also those who love this topic and are always ready to suggest something interesting. During second visit I ordered French pizza, their new special cocktail and GlenDronach whiskey. I recommend this place also because they want to fill full their menu with author's cocktails, not only a mainstream ones as many bars do.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_hYRbn5nnWyG6D2KN4mII-M8dOoPNR04rfwT1&fid=0x0:0x923ebcbe3a13feaf"],"When":"2020-11-7"},{"Name":"Lina Vilderman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRDgC27Lyoe4JSD5m4QMveiBBfxm2o88IgjNSqN5Kq17BjFR8H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Liked it. A bit messy, but it's normal for a new place. Food is delicious. Friendly stuff. Hope that cocktails will be added in near future. Recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVuJUvIgPHYoKFCU1cf_6rKnuEX9TEdJ_zBJeX&fid=0x0:0x923ebcbe3a13feaf"],"When":"2021-3-11"},{"Name":"Rodion Zinovyev","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZkAIrKcWuqsObsh1lc0CFpjc4WoCovYvMocvIl4OQKBgosj-imA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice pub in Ramat Gan, open on weekends, great casual atmosphere. Beverages selection is huge, draught beer selection is different from other pubs.
Best deal: selection of 6 shots for only 49 nis.
The only cons that it's located at the sidewalk of Bialik street, sometimes a little bit noisy, and some random people passing near you table. So if come here try to catch place at the bar inside.
Also there's alco shop close to the pub whith good prices.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPt2AMfecWZs5n76sZPSEeaZp_nWySu_qXjxgdj&fid=0x0:0x923ebcbe3a13feaf"],"When":"2021-9-7"},{"Name":"Maayan Yazdi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURQ9eyk-fZcrnxUOvqNQydR-knn9bzUxL5aBxHwAnpdYCdc9nfeA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great bar, always welcoming.
Wide selection of drinks and cocktails 🍸

The food is nice.
Always with a good music and nice atmosphere.

I recommend to visit during weekends while the area is less busy than usual.

I like the liquor store that connected to the place (next door).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Perelmutter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqTi7pekhLSp6_aMpI_9clFdkslUsgRCpEArwx9HqGxzAgbBZi=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I used to come to that place with a bunch of friends. On one occasion we celebrated a birthday of one of the gang, gave the waitress a tip. Two weeks later some of us came to the bar for a different thing, same waitress came to us and said we didn't give her enough tip and we have to complete it for the previous time. As this is not true we refused and so she refused to serve us. The manager wasn't present at the time. After half an hour of no service from the waitress who made a point of attending all the other tables near us, we left.

Her manager, who we knew and texted as the event unfolded, chose to believe her story and called us liars. Additionally we received threats when we posted about the experience in a local group.

It comes as no surprise that the same bar is know to have loud music past midnight and ignores and carries on complaints from neighbors in its vicinity.

It is my hope that the bat in question will closw down, the sooner-- the better, and if its owners will have huge debts for the rest of their as a result it wilp be even better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kyla Osminin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXKpmP2h7Zx3QYTGx7IgzgqrbOxDkzYJJcW1L97KX_wrJQGkvk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place! super friendly staff, great choice of tap beer, billiard, open late at night. Will definitely come back! ❤️❤️❤️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leonalyn Barkan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDQK5juI7iYDXco32p13eLFImIWoaMbEBKBy61bAObmZCoMAiDig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not bad for a first timer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOz4GBgdS-imX1CsCgHvIjCcIQhcDK_ObWU-VY3&fid=0x0:0x923ebcbe3a13feaf"],"When":"2021-12-18"}]
